Interface FaceEngine.OnAnalyzeFaceImageListener

  • Enclosing interface:
    FaceEngine
    public static interface FaceEngine.OnAnalyzeFaceImageListener
    Interface definition for a callback to be invoked when a request to FaceEngine.analyzeFace(Bitmap, OnAnalyzeFaceImageListener) or FaceEngine.analyzeFace(byte[], int, int, OnAnalyzeFaceImageListener) has finished.

      • onFaceAnalyzed

        void onFaceAnalyzed​(Biometrics.ResultCode resultCode,
                    android.graphics.RectF faceRect,
                    java.util.ArrayList<android.graphics.PointF> landmark5,
                    java.util.ArrayList<android.graphics.PointF> landmark68,
                    float[] headPoseEstimations,
                    FaceEngine.HeadPoseDirection[] headPoseDirections,
                    FaceEngine.Gender gender,
                    int age,
                    FaceEngine.Emotion dominantEmotion,
                    boolean hasGlasses,
                    int imageQuality)
        Callback method invoked when a request to either FaceEngine.analyzeFace(Bitmap, OnAnalyzeFaceImageListener) or FaceEngine.analyzeFace(byte[], int, int, OnAnalyzeFaceImageListener) has finished.
        Parameters:
        resultCode - Biometrics.ResultCode
        faceRect - Region of interest rectangle of face in image.
        landmark5 - Five major landmark points (left eye, right eye, nose).
        landmark68 - 68 landmark points across face.
        headPoseEstimations - Array of estimated head pose angles for roll, pitch, and yaw.
        headPoseDirections - Estimated head pose directions for each axis, roll, pitch, and yaw.
        gender - Estimated gender of detected face.
        age - Estimated age of detected face.
        dominantEmotion - Dominant emotion detected on face.
        hasGlasses - True if detected face has glasses, false otherwise.
        imageQuality - Score in range [0, 100] representing clarity of detected face.
